canonical:
  title: 贈友人
  author: 安牧
  language: lzh
  text: 紫陌連苔徑靑山對草廬好爲無事飮安用向空書漸覺芳心王猶嫌寒意餘見詩殊有興欲和愧才踈
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 贈友人
  author: 安牧
  language: lzh
  text: 紫陌連苔徑。靑山對草廬。好爲無事飮。安用向空書。漸覺芳心王。猶嫌寒意餘。見詩殊有興。欲和愧才踈。
korean:
  title: 증 우인
  author: 안목
  language: kor
  text: |-
    번화한 거리에 이어 이끼 낀 길
    푸른 산을 마주 대한 초가집 한 채
    일 없어 술 마시기 내 좋아하거니
    허공에 글자 쓸 까닭이 없어라
    지내느라니 차츰 젊은 맘도 생기고
    걱정은 도리어 너무 싸늘한 생각
    자네 시를 보니 흥이 불쑥 나네만
    붓 들어 화답하자니 재주 모자라 어쩌나
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0120_010_0840&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Gift for a Friend
  author: An Mok
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Purple streets fade into moss-covered paths,
    A thatched cottage faces the green mountain.
    I prefer to drink without purpose or gain—
    why waste words scrawling at empty air?

    Gradually, a young heart returns to me,
    yet winter's chill still lingers in my bones.
    Seeing your poem, delight stirs within,
    but to reply in verse? My talent falls short.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The 'purple streets' (紫陌) is a classical image representing the busy world of affairs and social obligations, contrasting with the retreat to nature represented by the moss-covered paths and mountain cottage.
  - key: ''
    value: The poem explores the tension between active engagement and contemplative withdrawal—the speaker values simple living and drinking over intellectual pursuits, yet cannot help but be moved by the friend's poetry.
